{
  "id": "019d340c-4fc0-7bc2-b275-6ce980a9119d",
  "content": "# Multi-Spoke Phase 0 Design Decisions (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: MCP bearer token auth + spoke Dockerfile + foundation security for multi-spoke workspace\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Token-gated writes only: Generate UUID v4 token when server binds to non-loopback address. Write tools require Bearer token, read tools stay open. Backward compatible with loopback binding.\n2. Token stored in {data_dir}/mcp-token file, injected into spoke containers as CORVIA_MCP_TOKEN env var\n3. Auth check happens inside handle_mcp_post() after tool name identification, not as Axum middleware layer. This avoids blocking reads and keeps the stateless MCP design intact.\n4. Spoke Dockerfile uses node:22-bookworm + pinned Claude Code version + non-root user. Entrypoint handles clone, MCP health check, and Claude Code startup.\n5. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is primary auth mode for spokes (documented for CI/container use). Subscription credential mounting is fallback.\n\n## Protected write tools: corvia_write, corvia_gc_run, corvia_config_set, corvia_rebuild_index, corvia_agent_suspend, corvia_merge_retry",
  "source_version": "mcp",
